<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-05-02T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-05-02T13:00:00-05:00" n="595" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways,
                                Inc./64: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-02T12:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">May 2,
                                            1928—12 noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 9
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>59. Upon instruction of the Pan American Airways, MacGregor left
                                today via San Salvador for Tegucigalpa to open negotiations for
                                transport concession.</p>
                            <p>The Government here is indisposed to take action on the company’s
                                application while the Cabinet resignations are pending. Repeated to
                                Tegucigalpa and San Salvador.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Geissler</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>